threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, EABI4 version 1 (SYSV), dynamically linked, interpreter /lib/ld-uClibc.so.0, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This ARMv7 ELF binary is a sophisticated IoT botnet agent, likely a variant of the Mirai family or similar malware. It exhibits comprehensive malicious behavior, including: 1) Persistence: It installs itself as a systemd service ('NexusCorp C2 Persistence Daemon'), modifies '/etc/rc.local' and '/etc/inittab', and sets up a crontab entry for reboots. 2) Stealth and Masquerading: It copies itself to '/usr/local/bin/sysd', changes its process name using prctl, and unlinks its own executable ('/proc/self/exe') to hinder forensics. 3) Process Hiding/Killing: It scans the '/proc' filesystem to identify and terminate competing processes such as 'sshd', 'telnetd', 'nginx', and 'apache'. 4) Botnet Activity: It establishes a C2 connection to a remote server to receive commands and contains multiple specialized functions (e.g., sub_164d0, sub_98c8, sub_deb4) designed for large-scale DDoS attacks, including SYN and UDP flooding. IOCs include the file path '/usr/local/bin/sysd', the service name 'persist.service', and the 'NexusCorp' string.
